-1828506949.text: "The activity of Rheb is in turn suppressed by the Tuberous Sclerosis Complex (TSC), comprised of the tumor suppressors TSC1 (hamartin) and TSC2 (tuberin), and the recently defined TBC1D7, which act coordinately as a GTPase activating protein (GAP) to convert active Rheb-GTP to inactive Rheb-GDP and suppress mTOR."
